2. Distortion Cost Doctrine becomes official
Gemini and Claude both sharpened this well.

Every transformation pays a tax.

This is now core doctrine:
	•	Map taxes accuracy
	•	Compress taxes nuance
	•	Expand taxes noise/speculation
	•	Split taxes wholeness/vitality
	•	Bind taxes flexibility
	•	Rotate taxes continuity
	•	Lift taxes groundedness
	•	Project taxes universality

This is important because it turns the library from a fantasy magic kit into an engineering manual.

New governing principle:

There is no free transformation. Choose moves by the tax you can afford.

