C. Claude’s missing operators

Three of Claude’s additions are genuinely strong.

Adopt into candidate/reference tier:
	•	Sample ∴ — representative slice used to probe a larger structure or distribution
	•	Name ℕ — minimal compression that grants boundaries and portability
	•	Permute ↕↔ — reorder elements to reveal sequence sensitivity or hidden non-commutativity

These are excellent additions because they capture reasoning moves the current library under-specified.

Also adopt as note/family:
	•	Substitute ≅ — replacement with structurally equivalent component
	•	Negate ¬ — explicit complement/opposite test

These may remain in the reference spec first rather than the practice kit.

