Clean verdict

Best contributions by source:

Grok
	•	strongest on meta-tier and scale ladder
	•	best contribution: operator algebra framing and transcendent/meta layer

Gemini
	•	strongest on distortion cost and practical katas
	•	best contribution: “no free transformation” engineering realism

Claude
	•	strongest on philosophical tightening and error correction
	•	best contribution: Anchor vs Lock distinction, failure recovery, structural vs ethical invariants, practice-kit vs reference-spec split

So the synthesis is:
	•	Grok gave scope
	•	Gemini gave operational cost
	•	Claude gave rigor

Together they make the doctrine much better.

